but before I even turn this thing on,

00:01:48.120 --> 00:01:49.860
there are clearly several things

00:01:49.860 --> 00:01:51.960
that are a little
different about this one.

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:53.940
So first of all, it's made of metal.

00:01:53.940 --> 00:01:57.420
Lots of metal and glass
here, which are high quality,

00:01:57.420 --> 00:02:00.570
but heavy materials, relatively speaking.

00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:03.510
So there's this precisely
machined aluminum frame

00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:04.470
around the outside.

00:02:04.470 --> 00:02:07.260
And yes, those are intakes
for fans at the bottom.

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:09.660
And then vents for those fans at the top.

00:02:09.660 --> 00:02:11.340
On the right side,
there's your digital crown

00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:13.140
that can be pressed in or turned.

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:16.320
And then on the other side is
just a single larger button.

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:18.780
So kind of basically the same
two buttons as an Apple Watch.

00:02:18.780 --> 00:02:20.040
And then when you get
a little further back

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:22.260
on this band here, these little pods

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:25.230
with downward facing
grills, these are speakers

00:02:25.230 --> 00:02:27.240
which are pointed straight at your ears,

00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:28.830
and work surprisingly well.

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.010
