But the main event is at the front.

00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:43.667
There is an enormous piece of glass,

00:02:43.667 --> 00:02:47.160
which, yes, is very easy
to fingerprint and smudge.

00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:49.140
And then behind that thing,
there's this outward-facing

00:02:49.140 --> 00:02:52.350
OLED display and a bunch of
sensors all the way around,

00:02:52.350 --> 00:02:54.780
outside facing sensors that go forward,

00:02:54.780 --> 00:02:57.150
sideways, and straight down.

00:02:57.150 --> 00:02:59.580
And there's depth sensors,
infrared illuminators,

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:03.180
lidar scanners, and just
regular old RGB cameras,

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.580
all being processed by an M2 chip

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:07.740
and an R1 chip inside this thing.

00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:09.270
And then maybe the craziest part,

00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:12.450
inside the headset, there
are a bunch more sensors

00:03:12.450 --> 00:03:15.990
facing your eyes, tracking
your eyes in real time,

00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:18.360
for all the eye control and
everything that comes with that.

00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:22.350
And also then to display a
representation of your eyes

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:24.870
on the outside of the headset.

