Now Apple's doing this.

00:31:15.150 --> 00:31:17.700
This is, again, it's technically in beta.

00:31:17.700 --> 00:31:19.950
So I dunno, there's room for improvement,

00:31:19.950 --> 00:31:21.000
but it still works.

00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:23.730
But as of right now, I feel like this is

00:31:23.730 --> 00:31:28.730
both incredibly impressive
and slightly unsettling.

00:31:28.830 --> 00:31:32.250
Like, it's very impressive
that this thing,

00:31:32.250 --> 00:31:33.690
this headset I'm wearing on my face,

00:31:33.690 --> 00:31:37.590
is tracking all these
little micro expressions

00:31:37.590 --> 00:31:39.990
and little movements for
my eyes and my cheeks

00:31:39.990 --> 00:31:42.120
and my mouth and everything.

00:31:42.120 --> 00:31:47.120
But at the same time,
it's just not quite human.

00:31:47.370 --> 00:31:49.410
It's right at the edge
of the uncanny valley

00:31:49.410 --> 00:31:51.900
of I'm not looking at a person.

00:31:51.900 --> 00:31:54.180
So yeah.

00:31:54.180 --> 00:31:58.380
But the crazy part is you
can now use this Persona

00:31:58.380 --> 00:32:01.860
as your camera feed for
any apps in Vision Pro

00:32:01.860 --> 00:32:06.600
that require a front facing
camera, like FaceTime.

00:32:06.600 --> 00:32:09.480
And so I've tried, I've
been using FaceTime

00:32:09.480 --> 00:32:11.010
a few times in the Vision Pro,

00:32:11.010 --> 00:32:15.480
and it is, technically
speaking, incredible.

00:32:15.480 --> 00:32:17.790
So I've made a few FaceTime
calls in the past few days

00:32:17.790 --> 00:32:19.230
with some fellow reviewers,

00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:21.720
who you'll probably recognize
from their Personas,

00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:23.910
who are also testing the Vision Pro.

00:32:23.910 --> 00:32:27.540
And universally, once we
all got past the shock of,

00:32:27.540 --> 00:32:29.400
oh my god, it's you.

00:32:29.400 --> 00:32:30.720
It looks like a digital version of you.

00:32:30.720 --> 00:32:31.553
This is crazy.

00:32:31.553 --> 00:32:33.120
I've never seen anything like this before.

00:32:33.120 --> 00:32:36.810
Once we got past that, there
is a ton happening here.

00:32:36.810 --> 00:32:39.180
So you can see the FaceTime windows

00:32:39.180 --> 00:32:41.190
literally appear as just that.

00:32:41.190 --> 00:32:44.130
They're just like glassy
windows floating in space

00:32:44.130 --> 00:32:46.050
with people looking through them.

00:32:46.050 --> 00:32:49.530
And then the angle that
you look into the window

00:32:49.530 --> 00:32:54.090
is gonna match the angle that
they see you looking at them.

00:32:54.090 --> 00:32:57.330
Meaning if we're all in
Vision Pros on this call,

